strings.Value: "Who is this 'prince' you keep talking about?"
"Those beads on your head — you took them from a woman on this road!"
"Are you alone here?"
"I need to go."
"I am the {mf|baron|baroness|king|queen} of these lands! Do you know what I do with impostors like yourself?!"
"Give me the beads now or taste my fist."
"The prince of Kamelands is content with simple beads? I heard that the neighboring prince was gifted with a real crown! With rubies and emeralds!"
"Fine, I'll leave you alone with your 'tribute'."
"Want to trade? Here, I have food."
[Attack] "Vile little thief! You've made a mistake coming to these lands!"
"Are you aware, Prince, that this necklace belongs Zogmugot herself — one of the goblin hero-gods? See how she stares at you from each bead, as though about to come out and strangle you!"

{n}The goblin in front of you looks... unusual. His ugly face is covered with red clay — which looks to be warpaint. A string of beads is hanging down from his ears, and he's wearing a dirty reed skirt.{/n}
"Stop! I be prince of Kameland! You be bringing presents?! I take everything — shiny bits, sparkly bits, grub!"

"I be prince! Ruler of Kameland! All you see here — it mine. That tree — mine. And rock? The rock mine. And river... And..."{n} The goblin keeps listing everything he sees and pointing his finger at it.{/n}
"Tribute to prince of Kameland! Mine!" {n}The goblin clutches the beads and steps back, baring his teeth.{/n}
"{mf|Baron-shmaron|Baroness-shmaroness|King-shming|Queen-shmeen}! What kind of dumb word be that?"
"Prince be great and mighty! Prince no be scarefraid of anybody!"

{n}The goblin leaps up angrly.{/n} "Neighbor? What neighbor?! I prince! I main goblin!" {n}He rips the beads off his head and throws them at your feet.{/n} "Keep your trash! I go sort things out! Smash neighbor, take his crown, be main goblin all around!"
{n}The goblin glares at you suspiciously. Either he knows you're lying — or equally possible, he doesn't know what an emerald is.{/n}

"AAAAA! Prince wants to live! Prince be too pretty to die!" {n}The goblin rips the beads off his head and throws them at you. With an angry whine, the goblin runs off, a trail of reed stalks falling from his skirt as he flees.{/n}
"Dumb human! You be no fright-scary! Go fast and bring prince grub to gulp, before I beat you up!"

{n}The goblin is shuffling his feet.{/n} "There be goblins in gorge, looking for greatbeast. Also be goblins in village... But not all know and listen to prince yet! First time when I came, they hit me, and it hurt!"
"So, you bring grub yet?"

{n}The goblin eyes the food in your hand hungrily. Finally, he can help himself no more — he tears the beads off his head, then snatches up the food and runs off, stuffing the treat into his mouth as he does.{/n}

"The tree, it mine, the rock mine too, I rule this place, I'm telling you..." {n}Linzi hums, improvising a simple tune.{/n} "This might make a nice song! 'The Ballad of the Goblin Prince,' what do you think?"

"Would you look at that — we've got another sovereign here! There must be something in the air making rulers multiply like rabbits. Soon you won't be able to plant an apple tree without a king apple growing from it, declaring independence, and demanding taxes!"
{n}Nok-Nok's ear twitches.{/n} "Prince? What that? Another stupid noise stupid longshanks make up and vomit on goblins?"
{n}Kanerah bends in a mocking curtsy.{/n} "Hello, your green highness!"
